A daily menu of an obese child: do not breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children aged between 9 and 13 years have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity at 5 per cent.
Obese children originate in most families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It is once again demonstrated the importance of the environment where one grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obese children are fed, for example, by sausages at least twice as often as children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program - Obesity is not a chance -
In overweight families there is no practice of sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of the last school year and participated in the same almost 900 children of Basic Education from all over Czechia.
It was already the second edition of the “The Obesity of Not a Chance” program that supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
To date, more than 12 thousand children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th grade.
A proper diet and sufficient family exercise are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
“Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” she says.
No breakfast but with sandwich for dinner
The experts warn that, in healthy development, the details are also important, which they also count, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of school families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one ate alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that 10 percent of households don't have breakfasts.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in obese children's families, fried insanities are consumed much more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet refreshments daily (70%).
Generally sports more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Build your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the selected males (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years from the point of view of a healthy diet are far from ideal.
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“It’s particularly alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments” is advised in the final report of the study.
As the main meal, the paste is taken by the palm and the poultry meat is closely followed.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after the end of the prevention programme, obesity is not a coincidence, in many cases a major change in favor of the principles of a healthy diet, is indicated in the results of the study.
It calls attention, for example, to the sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and ordinary water.
Children would also choose the meat of poultry and fish for the main meal more frequently in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
