In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A journey, in principle unoccupied, is complicated because of a series of improper neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this was of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was meant to be done.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, aroused high expectations already before its debut.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of the show, appears as a game that should not end up being a sort of action again without more.
We also feel curious about how the scenes would stay inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much about what we expected.
There are careers that can be given for acceptable, but in total purchase points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In fact, they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible deception of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit on the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one doesn't even feel remotely that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasant in sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the desert walk, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a number of required rivals (normal in a classic race), then try to earn time (classical timed duel) and then await a duel against one opponent.
In the midst of all this the police sometimes appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are a lot less landscapes in the game than we could expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the traces of previous episodes.
That means today is no longer a big deal, but it can't be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career designed with a lot of action is quite suitable for this driving style, although we can find something better among competition games.
So far, all in order.
But problems arise after a certain amount of time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true with collisions.
Of games of this kind you can't expect it to recreate complex deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled piroutes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed so that when you suffer an accident or get out of the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each career there are only five resets available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's only help in case something isn't going well, but it's not much to be trusted.
Sometimes, neither the reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, one has to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you meet at some place vehicles - civics - always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth, or you get five minutes before or after.
This angers especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent runs fast, but when you arrive, you must turn around or stop.
It's the same when you arrive, because it's programmed because the \"surprise\" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have a further advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, without regard to the moment, you will always get ahead of the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes before you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can make the car papilla.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will likely be disappointed immediately.
And it's a shame, because even though the travel model is simple, the game is fun and action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive clues or the ranking in the race so that it doesn't break boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be careful with the gas outlets next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight highways and exotic superports for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, i.e., there are races in specific places that you will know about the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending up with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you get to the metro tunnel (step), where you run to the dark through the tracks (steps).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (step) and, all of a sudden, the subway convoy arrives behind you and you are taken forward without more.
In writing we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the game programming none thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
What a pity it is that at the most tense times the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to be of pleasure to most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category - each of its father and mother - but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confused.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble stating that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
The fun is assured, but prepare because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs at the University of Carolina will participate in the concert (Terciopelo Students)
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third World Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Academic Festival.
During the same period, twenty choirs will be presented from secondary and university schools.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
“The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival”
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the festival committee is the Rector Václav Hampl - said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The festival's entire summit is the free entry for all audiences to the secondary choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library at Device.
The programme has the participation of Czech Jazzista Karel Rŭžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening it will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady the concert (Terciopelo Students) in which you will participate university choirs, including the choir of the University Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Day of Students and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Third World Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the director of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the festive concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
