Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone was looking for a term that would define IBM's strategy with great precision, the nearest would be - long-term -
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, it has already spent a hundred years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-term character was laid by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
Its motto - think - became its seal, around which the life of the giant future will be built (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
