The Italian association of foreign banks joined the pressure by warning that a failure of Monti would be a disaster.
Monti started his consultations on Monday with political parties, trade unions and business groups, as well as with youth and women's organizations.
He'll put an end to his round of meetings on Tuesday night.
Monti was appointed Sunday by Napolitano, which has enabled an extremely rapid transition in response to the crisis.
