We trust each other with each other's music and couldn't be better.
Your relationship with the word fame has not been simple; however, thanks to your success, you have been able to do what you want.
How do you find a balance sheet?
As we've been growing, it's been easier to find a balance sheet.
We make sure that you're not too much on tour because it's easy to fall into that game of the great crowds and the people who love your music.
While one remembers that people are there for music, that reminds you that you must respect music and what brought it, without becoming captivating for being famous and being a rock star, something that none of us really care about.
How does your other Mother Love Bone project remind you?
I think we wrote very good songs and at first it was something great.
We were a band for almost three years and never published a record until after Andy (Andrew Woods) died.
