For a hitchhiker from Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, on the press wheel for the operation against -Cano - is very significant.
Many people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without margin of error, that can become key in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, the lofoscopics support investigations into crimes such as stealing and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals present false ballots or have no papers.
We take the fingerprint and look them up in the database.
The investigator reported that in a case of theft, he was touched to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to remove a safe full of jewelry and money.
The walls are difficult because they are not appropriate surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the mark from the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts, he remembered.
The fingerprints can also rule out or reaffirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently they found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a family member could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a mark in the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that it was the killer, it does locate him at the crime scene.
One CTI dactyloscopeist explained that in the objects - the prints are removed with chemical or physical reagents -
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
