The scheme adopted by the Austrian Government is closer to the German model, since Germany was the first European country to adopt that type of rule.
Prior to 2017, the structural public deficit should decrease annually by 0.75 per cent of gross domestic product (GDP) and, as of 2017, the structural government deficit of the federal state should not exceed 0.35 per cent of GDP each year, while regional states, as well as municipalities, should present balanced budgets.
The objective is to reduce public debt by 60 per cent by 2020/2021.
